<Link id="l00682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="682"><span class="doxyHighlight">  int32&#95;t ImmValue = RawImmValue;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For &#39;set&#39; you can&#39;t use &#39;or&#39; with a negative operand on V9 because</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that would splat the sign bit across the upper half of the destination</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// register, whereas &#39;set&#39; is defined to zero the high 32 bits.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> IsEffectivelyImm13 =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"><span class="doxyHighlight">      IsImm &amp;&amp; ((<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/lib/target/x86/disassembler/x86disassembler-cpp/#a652270ec0bdb03b5a7f934524412aa7f">is64Bit</a>() ? 0 : -4096) &lt;= ImmValue &amp;&amp; ImmValue &lt; 4096);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> &#42;ValExpr;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (IsImm)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span></CodeLine>
